BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Free virtual lecture: The Lives and Times of Midwest Amphibians wi
 th Dr. Spencer Cortwright
DTSTART:20260528T190000
DTEND:20260528T203000
UID:98da05f623066c829b7ce3119d223c81@sycamorelandtrust.org
DESCRIPTION:Each spring amphibians bring great joy as they seem to suddenl
 y emerge from a frozen landscape. Join us for a free virtual lecture and Q
 &amp\;A with Dr. Spencer Cortwright\, Professor of Biology at Indiana Univ
 ersity Northwest and longtime researcher of amphibian and restoration ecol
 ogy. Dr. Cortwright will take us on a richly illustrated journey through t
 he lives of Midwestern amphibians\, exploring their year-round life cycles
 \, seasonal movements\, and the remarkable adaptations that help them tran
 sition from a frozen landscape to springtime abundance.
URL:https://sycamorelandtrust.org/2026/03/the-lives-and-times-of-midwest-a
 mphibians-with-dr-spencer-cortwright/
X-SOURCE:Sycamore Land Trust
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Hike the Trust: Canyon Forest Nature Preserve
DTSTART:20260510T090000
DTEND:20260510T110000
UID:c9ea4044c14c5793161c1df574548ba3@sycamorelandtrust.org
DESCRIPTION:Join us for a guided hike as part of our Hike the Trust series
  at Canyon Forest Nature Preserve\, a rugged and scenic 68-acre preserve. 
 Its deep ravines and sandstone outcrops are part of Greene County’s anci
 ent bedrock\, where resistant sandstones and underlying shale have been sc
 ulpted over millions of years to form dramatic canyons and slopes that sup
 port diverse plant communities\, from orchids and ferns to woodland trees.
  Along the way\, we’ll tie together how the geology influences soil\, wa
 ter flow\, and plant distribution\, helping you see the connection between
  rocks\, soils\, forests\, and ecological diversity in one of Indiana’s 
 most interesting natural areas.
LOCATION:Canyon Forest Nature Preserve
URL:https://sycamorelandtrust.org/2026/04/hike-the-trust-canyon-forest-nat
 ure-preserve/
X-SOURCE:Sycamore Land Trust
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Welcome to Warblers with Randy Jones
DTSTART:20260509T080000
DTEND:20260509T103000
UID:682f578ce2280e954d6089205cb0821a@sycamorelandtrust.org
DESCRIPTION:Spring is in full swing in Brown County\, and Stone Head Natur
 e Preserve is alive with migrating songbirds! Join Randy Jones for a guide
 d birding hike to spot and listen for warblers across the preserve’s woo
 dlands\, wetlands\, and restored prairie. Learn quick ID tips\, how to rea
 d their habitats\, and tricks for catching those bright flashes of spring 
 color in the canopy and the reeds. All experience levels are encouraged to
  come\, and binoculars will be available!
LOCATION:Stone Head Nature Preserve
URL:https://sycamorelandtrust.org/2026/04/welcome-to-warblers-with-randy-j
 ones-2/
X-SOURCE:Sycamore Land Trust
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Little Hikers: Spring Wildflowers
DTSTART:20260508T093000
DTEND:20260508T113000
UID:e1a6c69cf9e5522adb5b8e7c559aba6e@sycamorelandtrust.org
DESCRIPTION:Join us at Porter West Preserve for a Little Hikers adventure 
 in search of spring wildflowers! As the forest wakes up\, we’ll explore 
 the trails to discover colorful blooms peeking through the leaf litter and
  learn how these early “spring ephemerals” make the most of sunlight b
 efore the trees leaf out. This kid-friendly hike will move at a curious pa
 ce\, with plenty of time to look closely\, ask questions\, and celebrate t
 he tiny wonders of the season!
LOCATION:Porter West Preserve
URL:https://sycamorelandtrust.org/2026/04/little-hikers-spring-wildflowers
 /
X-SOURCE:Sycamore Land Trust
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Spring Plant Sale to Benefit our Native Plant Nursery
DTSTART:20260502T090000
DTEND:20260502T140000
UID:06c7e4c25db9d9600de3f00ba8f5c94c@sycamorelandtrust.org
DESCRIPTION:We are thrilled to announce our fifth annual Spring Plant Sale
 ! We are offering over 40 species of plants that were homegrown in our Nat
 ive Plant Nursery from seed to plant plug. Many species are grown from loc
 ally collected seed at nearby preserves. All species are ethically sourced
  and native to southern Indiana\, providing benefits to local pollinators 
 and wildlife. Plants sell for $4 each\, with all proceeds going back into 
 nursery operations and native plant restoration projects. Stop by to learn
  from experienced staff and volunteers on the advantages of gardening with
  native species! For more information\, visit sycamorelandtrust.org/plant-
 sale.
LOCATION:Bloomingfoods East Parking Lot
URL:https://sycamorelandtrust.org/2026/03/spring-plant-sale-to-benefit-our
 -native-plant-nursery/
X-SOURCE:Sycamore Land Trust
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Forest Floor to Canopy with Ava Hartman and Saige Sentell
DTSTART:20260430T173000
DTEND:20260430T193000
UID:1e0401b5a66bf5ca60743383b6551bde@sycamorelandtrust.org
DESCRIPTION:From the tiniest ant to the tallest oak\, forest systems are b
 uilt on connections. Join Sycamore Land Trust and CanopyBloomington for a 
 guided hike at Porter West Preserve that explores forest ecology from the 
 ground up. We’ll start by looking down\, identifying spring ephemerals t
 hat bloom early to take advantage of sunlight before the canopy closes\, t
 hen we&#8217\;ll look up to examine tree species\, forest structure\, and 
 how a healthy canopy supports a diverse understory.
LOCATION:Porter West Preserve
URL:https://sycamorelandtrust.org/2026/04/forest-floor-to-canopy-with-ava-
 hartman-and-saige-sentell/
X-SOURCE:Sycamore Land Trust
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Karst Ecology Hike with Tom Swinford
DTSTART:20260429T093000
DTEND:20260429T113000
UID:59d685c529d42723fe7c714c9e973999@sycamorelandtrust.org
DESCRIPTION:Dive into the weird and wonderful world beneath your feet with
  Land Acquisitions Director Tom Swinford! Porter West is full of surprises
  including sinkholes\, disappearing streams\, and underground passages tha
 t all shape the forest in unexpected ways. As the ground comes alive with 
 trillium\, spring beauty\, and bloodroot\, Tom will connect the dots betwe
 en limestone\, water\, and the plants that thrive in this ever-shifting sy
 stem.
LOCATION:Porter West Preserve
URL:https://sycamorelandtrust.org/2026/04/trekkin-for-trillium-with-tom-sw
 inford/
X-SOURCE:Sycamore Land Trust
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Wildflowers at the Water&#8217\;s Edge: A Spring Ephemeral Hike
DTSTART:20260428T170000
DTEND:20260428T200000
UID:64e75aa37c3ddef0662ab4d348e6634c@sycamorelandtrust.org
DESCRIPTION:Celebrate spring at Amy Weingartner Branigin Peninsula Preserv
 e\, where limestone bluffs meet the shores of Lake Monroe. This unique pen
 insula rises from the water on ancient limestone bedrock\, creating calciu
 m-rich soils and varied slopes that nurture an exceptional diversity of sp
 ring wildflowers. Come see Virginia Bluebells\, Pussytoes\, Columbine\, an
 d more!
LOCATION:Amy Weingartner Branigin Peninsula Preserve
URL:https://sycamorelandtrust.org/2026/04/wildflowers-at-the-waters-edge-a
 -spring-ephemeral-hike/
X-SOURCE:Sycamore Land Trust
END:VEVENT
