BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Beanblossom Bottoms 30th Anniversary: Advanced Wetland Botany with
  Kevin Tungesvick
DTSTART:20260712T100000
DTEND:20260712T120000
UID:ac2c98ead15e6fe11060895c2ba69e96@sycamorelandtrust.org
DESCRIPTION:Dive deep into the diverse plant life of Beanblossom Bottoms w
 ith this advanced botany class. Explore wetland ecosystems\, identify key 
 species\, and discuss their ecological roles with Kevin\, a lifelong botan
 ist and current ecologist with Eco Logic LLC. Perfect for seasoned plant e
 nthusiasts and professionals. Bring a field notebook and waterproof boots!
  Kevin is a Restoration Ecologist with Eco Logic\, and worked as a botanis
 t for Spence Restoration Nursery. This event was rescheduled from June 14 
 due to spring flooding. If this hike is full\, sign up for the wait list h
 ere.
LOCATION:Beanblossom Bottoms Nature Preserve
URL:https://sycamorelandtrust.org/2025/04/beanblossom-bottoms-30th-anniver
 sary-advanced-wetland-botany-with-kevin-tungesvick/
X-SOURCE:Sycamore Land Trust
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Prairie Forb Identification at Powell Preserve
DTSTART:20260708T080000
DTEND:20260708T100000
UID:1e84fc1cf47279191f3df9e4ffb28458@sycamorelandtrust.org
DESCRIPTION:Join Education Director Saige Sentell to discover the diverse 
 mix of habitats Powell Preserve provides: forested hills\, bottomland wood
 s\, and a prairie planting with native wildflowers and grasses. We’ll me
 ander the trail identifying native grasses and forbs\, studying plant part
 s and their ecological role. Powell Preserve is not open to the public.
LOCATION:Powell Preserve
URL:https://sycamorelandtrust.org/2025/06/prairie-forb-identification/
X-SOURCE:Sycamore Land Trust
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Group Hike: Porter West Preserve
DTSTART:20260624T090000
DTEND:20260624T120000
UID:cd7a763abece8903c6f0a09fcf378495@sycamorelandtrust.org
DESCRIPTION:Join Education Director Saige Sentell for a 2.5-mile guided hi
 ke at Porter West Preserve. We&#8217\;ll explore the preserve&#8217\;s bea
 utiful and diverse habitats on moderate to rugged terrain\, taking time to
  learn about the native plants\, trees\, birds\, and anything else we disc
 over along the way. This is a casual\, exploration hike where everyone is 
 encouraged to share their interests and knowledge\, or to listen and enjoy
  the hike. Bring your favorite field guides\, binoculars\, and curiosity!
LOCATION:Porter West Preserve
URL:https://sycamorelandtrust.org/2025/06/group-hike-at-porter-west-preser
 ve/
X-SOURCE:Sycamore Land Trust
